This paper focuses on software complexity metrics, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed metric is specifically for measuring class complexity, which is a concept related to programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the development of an automated tool, which could fall under software development (cs.SD). The evaluation of the metric using Weyuker's property could be considered a statistical analysis (cs.MS). Finally, the topic of software maintenance and cost reduction could also be relevant to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
